Warstein is a town in the district of Soest, in North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. North Rhine-Westphalia is the most populous state of Germany (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Rhine-Westphalia). Its capital is Duesseldorf and its biggest city Cologne. 4 of Germany's 10 biggest cities -- Cologne, Duesseldorf, Dortmund, and Essen -- are located in North Rhine-Westphalia. The state is divided into 31 districts (Kreise) and 23 urban districts (kreisfreie Staedte). A map of the districts can be found at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Rhine-Westphalia#Subdivisions. - Mod.ML]
